createSessionBindService()` factory to `session-bind.js` — creates and auto-initializes a `SessionBindingService` instance with `bindingsPath` config. Update `index.js` export.\n- [ ] T2: Integrate `message-router` into Telegram bot text handler — replace direct `executeAiCli` + `sessionStore` calls with `messageRouter.processMessage()`. The message-router already handles session store append, prompt building, and realtimeHub publishing.\n- [ ] T3: Add cross-channel Telegram push — when a Web-originated message produces an AI reply, push the reply to the bound Telegram chat via `bot.telegram.sendMessage()`. Subscribe to realtimeHub events for bound sessions.\n- [ ] T4: Verify and fix existing tests — run all F-018 tests, fix any failures caused by the broken `createSessionBindService` import or message-router integration changes.\n- [ ] T5: Run full test suite — ensure no regressions across the project.\n","structuredPatch":[],"originalFile":null}}
