{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01Aa8Mpjik5Mexwk5NLNR7TW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→# F-018: Web-Telegram Bidirectional Sync — Implementation Plan\n     2→\n     3→## Architecture Overview\n     4→\n     5→### Current State\n     6→- Web: HTTP API → `chat-service.js` → `codebuddy.js` adapter → spawns CLI process\n     7→- Telegram: Bot text handler → `executeAiCli()` directly → spawns CLI process\n     8→- Two completely isolated execution paths, no shared session state between channels\n     9→\n    10→### Target State\n    11→- Both channels → `message-router.js` → `executeAiCli()` → spawns CLI process\n    12→- Shared session store keyed by `telegram:{chatId}` when bound\n    13→- `realtimeHub` publishes all events (user_message, assistant_chunk, assistant_done)\n    14→- Web SSE subscribers receive Telegram events; Telegram receives Web events via bot push\n    15→- `session-bind.js` provides `createSessionBindService()` factory for HTTP server\n    16→\n    17→### Key Design Decisions\n    18→- D1: Keep `chat-service.js` and `codebuddy.js` as-is for backward compatibility but stop using them for the main chat flow. The Telegram bot text handler and Web chat endpoint both use `message-router.js`.\n    19→- D2: Session key strategy — when a web session is bound to a Telegram chat, both use `telegram:{chatId}` as session key. Unbound web sessions use `web:{sessionId}`.\n    20→- D3: Telegram bot subscribes to realtimeHub for the current chat's session key to push Web-originated messages to Telegram.\n    21→- D4: `createSessionBindService()` is a thin factory that creates + initializes a `SessionBindingService` instance, matching the import pattern in `server.js`.\n    22→\n    23→### Data Flow\n    24→\n    25→```\n    26→Web POST /api/chat\n    27→  → api-routes.js → messageRouter.processMessage()\n    28→  → sessionStore.append(sessionKey, 'user', msg)\n    29→  → realtimeHub.publish(sessionKey, user_message)\n    30→  → executeAiCli(sessionKey, prompt)\n    31→    → onChunk: realtimeHub.publish(sessionKey, assistant_chunk)\n    32→  → sessionStore.append(sessionKey, 'assistant', reply)\n    33→  → realtimeHub.publish(sessionKey, assistant_done)\n    34→\n    35→Telegram text message\n    36→  → telegram.js text handler → messageRouter.processMessage()\n    37→  → Same flow as above (shared sessionKey + realtimeHub)\n    38→\n    39→Web SSE /api/events?telegramChatId=X\n    40→  → Subscribe to realtimeHub(telegram:X)\n    41→  → Receives all events from both channels\n    42→\n    43→Telegram bot subscription\n    44→  → On bot start, subscribe to realtimeHub for active chat sessions\n    45→  → When web-originated assistant_done arrives, push reply to Telegram chat\n    46→```\n    47→\n    48→### Files to Create/Modify\n    49→\n    50→| File | Action | Description |\n    51→|------|--------|-------------|\n    52→| `src/services/session-bind.js` | Modify | Add `createSessionBindService()` factory function |\n    53→| `src/services/index.js` | Modify | Update export to use new factory |\n    54→| `src/bot/telegram.js` | Modify | Replace direct executeAiCli + chatWithSession with message-router; add cross-channel push |\n    55→| `src/http/server.js` | Verify | Already correct, just needs working import |\n    56→| `src/routes/api-routes.js` | Verify | Already correct |\n    57→| `src/services/message-router.js` | Verify | Already correct |\n    58→\n    59→### Testing Approach\n    60→\n    61→- Unit tests: `session-bind-f018.test.js` (exists), `message-router.test.js` (exists)\n    62→- Integration test: `f018-web-telegram-sync.integration.test.js` (exists but may fail due to broken import)\n    63→- New test: Telegram bot message-router integration test\n    64→- Test command: `node --test tests/services/session-bind-f018.test.js tests/services/message-router.test.js tests/integration/f018-web-telegram-sync.integration.test.js`\n    65→\n    66→## Tasks\n    67→\n    68→- [x] T1: Add `createSessionBindService()` factory to `session-bind.js` — creates and auto-initializes a `SessionBindingService` instance with `bindingsPath` config. Update `index.js` export.\n    69→- [x] T2: Integrate `message-router` into Telegram bot text handler — replace direct `executeAiCli` + `sessionStore` calls with `messageRouter.processMessage()`. The message-router already handles session store append, prompt building, and realtimeHub publishing.\n    70→- [x] T3: Add cross-channel Telegram push — when a Web-originated message produces an AI reply, push the reply to the bound Telegram chat via `bot.telegram.sendMessage()`. Subscribe to realtimeHub events for bound sessions.\n    71→- [x] T4: Verify and fix existing tests — run all F-018 tests, fix any failures caused by the broken `createSessionBindService` import or message-router integration changes.\n    72→- [x] T5: Run full test suite — ensure no regressions across the project.\n    73→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01YQWojDuu9hhr9G6EMSopGA","session_id":"1825d45b-0e87-4048-aee3-8c65afe6c801","uuid":"53290a2e-051e-46a2-85e7-7a9896963864","timestamp":"2026-03-22T06:45:24.900Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01MGL8HHEQfSTYgVdpzb2vh7","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import { readFile, writeFile, mkdir } from 'node:fs/promises';\n     2→import path from 'node:path';\n     3→import { config } from '../config.js';\n     4→import { logger } from '../utils/logger.js';\n     5→\n     6→const BINDINGS_FILE = 'session-bindings.json';\n     7→\n     8→class SessionBindingService {\n     9→  #bindings = null; // Map: webSessionId -> telegramChatId\n    10→  #reverseBindings = null; // Map: telegramChatId -> Set<webSessionId>\n    11→  #initialized = false;\n    12→  #persistencePath;\n    13→  #lastPersistPromise = Promise.resolve();\n    14→  #initPromise = null;\n    15→\n    16→  constructor({ persistenceDir = config.sessionPersistenceDir } = {}) {\n    17→    this.#persistencePath = path.join(persistenceDir, BINDINGS_FILE);\n    18→  }\n    19→\n    20→  async init() {\n    21→    if (this.#initialized) {\n    22→      return;\n    23→    }\n    24→\n    25→    // If init is already in progress, wait for it\n    26→    if (this.#initPromise) {\n    27→      return this.#initPromise;\n    28→    }\n    29→\n    30→    this.#initPromise = this.#doInit();\n    31→    return this.#initPromise;\n    32→  }\n    33→\n    34→  async #doInit() {\n    35→    try {\n    36→      const data = await readFile(this.#persistencePath, 'utf-8');\n    37→      const parsed = JSON.parse(data);\n    38→      this.#bindings = new Map(Object.entries(parsed.bindings || {}));\n    39→      this.#reverseBindings = new Map();\n    40→\n    41→      // Build reverse index\n    42→      for (const [webSessionId, telegramChatId] of this.#bindings.entries()) {\n    43→        if (!this.#reverseBindings.has(telegramChatId)) {\n    44→          this.#reverseBindings.set(telegramChatId, new Set());\n    45→        }\n    46→        this.#reverseBindings.get(telegramChatId).add(webSessionId);\n    47→      }\n    48→\n    49→      logger.info(\n    50→        { bindingsCount: this.#bindings.size },\n    51→        'Session bindings loaded'\n    52→      );\n    53→    } catch (error) {\n    54→      if (error.code === 'ENOENT') {\n    55→        // File doesn't exist, create directory if needed\n    56→        await mkdir(path.dirname(this.#persistencePath), { recursive: true });\n    57→        this.#bindings = new Map();\n    58→        this.#reverseBindings = new Map();\n    59→        await this.#persist();\n    60→        logger.info('Session bindings file created');\n    61→      } else {\n    62→        logger.warn({ err: error.message }, 'Failed to load session bindings, starting empty');\n    63→        this.#bindings = new Map();\n    64→        this.#reverseBindings = new Map();\n    65→      }\n    66→    }\n    67→\n    68→    this.#initialized = true;\n    69→  }\n    70→\n    71→  /**\n    72→   * Ensure the service is initialized. If init was triggered by the factory,\n    73→   * this will await completion. For manual usage, callers should call init() first.\n    74→   */\n    75→  async #ensureInitialized() {\n    76→    if (this.#initialized) {\n    77→      return;\n    78→    }\n    79→    if (this.#initPromise) {\n    80→      await this.#initPromise;\n    81→      return;\n    82→    }\n    83→    throw new Error('SessionBindingService not initialized. Call init() first.');\n    84→  }\n    85→\n    86→  async #persist() {\n    87→    try {\n    88→      const serialized = {\n    89→        bindings: Object.fromEntries(this.#bindings),\n    90→        updatedAt: new Date().toISOString()\n    91→      };\n    92→      await writeFile(\n    93→        this.#persistencePath,\n    94→        JSON.stringify(serialized, null, 2)\n    95→      );\n    96→    } catch (error) {\n    97→      logger.error({ err: error.message }, 'Failed to persist session bindings');\n    98→    }\n    99→  }\n   100→\n   101→  bindSession(webSessionId, telegramChatId) {\n   102→    if (!this.#initialized) {\n   103→      throw new Error('SessionBindingService not initialized. Call init() first.');\n   104→    }\n   105→\n   106→    const normalizedWebId = String(webSessionId).trim();\n   107→    const normalizedChatId = String(telegramChatId).trim();\n   108→\n   109→    if (!normalizedWebId) {\n   110→      throw new Error('webSessionId cannot be empty');\n   111→    }\n   112→\n   113→    if (!normalizedChatId) {\n   114→      throw new Error('telegramChatId cannot be empty');\n   115→    }\n   116→\n   117→    // Remove any existing binding for this web session\n   118→    if (this.#bindings.has(normalizedWebId)) {\n   119→      const oldChatId = this.#bindings.get(normalizedWebId);\n   120→      this.#reverseBindings.get(oldChatId)?.delete(normalizedWebId);\n   121→    }\n   122→\n   123→    // Create new binding\n   124→    this.#bindings.set(normalizedWebId, normalizedChatId);\n   125→\n   126→    // Update reverse index\n   127→    if (!this.#reverseBindings.has(normalizedChatId)) {\n   128→      this.#reverseBindings.set(normalizedChatId, new Set());\n   129→    }\n   130→    this.#reverseBindings.get(normalizedChatId).add(normalizedWebId);\n   131→\n   132→    this.#lastPersistPromise = this.#persist();\n   133→\n   134→    logger.info(\n   135→      { webSessionId: normalizedWebId, telegramChatId: normalizedChatId },\n   136→      'Session bound to Telegram chat'\n   137→    );\n   138→\n   139→    return { ok: true };\n   140→  }\n   141→\n   142→  unbindSession(webSessionId) {\n   143→    if (!this.#initialized) {\n   144→      throw new Error('SessionBindingService not initialized. Call init() first.');\n   145→    }\n   146→\n   147→    const normalizedWebId = String(webSessionId).trim();\n   148→\n   149→    if (!normalizedWebId) {\n   150→      throw new Error('webSessionId cannot be empty');\n   151→    }\n   152→\n   153→    if (!this.#bindings.has(normalizedWebId)) {\n   154→      return { ok: false, error: 'No binding found for this session' };\n   155→    }\n   156→\n   157→    const telegramChatId = this.#bindings.get(normalizedWebId);\n   158→    this.#bindings.delete(normalizedWebId);\n   159→\n   160→    // Update reverse index\n   161→    this.#reverseBindings.get(telegramChatId)?.delete(normalizedWebId);\n   162→\n   163→    this.#lastPersistPromise = this.#persist();\n   164→\n   165→    logger.info(\n   166→      { webSessionId: normalizedWebId },\n   167→      'Session unbound from Telegram chat'\n   168→    );\n   169→\n   170→    return { ok: true };\n   171→  }\n   172→\n   173→  getBoundChatId(webSessionId) {\n   174→    if (!this.#initialized) {\n   175→      throw new Error('SessionBindingService not initialized. Call init() first.');\n   176→    }\n   177→\n   178→    const normalizedWebId = String(webSessionId).trim();\n   179→    return this.#bindings.get(normalizedWebId) || null;\n   180→  }\n   181→\n   182→  getBoundWebSessions(telegramChatId) {\n   183→    if (!this.#initialized) {\n   184→      throw new Error('SessionBindingService not initialized. Call init() first.');\n   185→    }\n   186→\n   187→    const normalizedChatId = String(telegramChatId).trim();\n   188→    const sessions = this.#reverseBindings.get(normalizedChatId);\n   189→    return sessions ? Array.from(sessions) : [];\n   190→  }\n   191→\n   192→  getAllBindings() {\n   193→    if (!this.#initialized) {\n   194→      throw new Error('SessionBindingService not initialized. Call init() first.');\n   195→    }\n   196→\n   197→    return Object.fromEntries(this.#bindings);\n   198→  }\n   199→\n   200→  clearAllBindings() {\n   201→    if (!this.#initialized) {\n   202→      throw new Error('SessionBindingService not initialized. Call init() first.');\n   203→    }\n   204→\n   205→    this.#bindings.clear();\n   206→    this.#reverseBindings.clear();\n   207→    this.#lastPersistPromise = this.#persist();\n   208→\n   209→    logger.info('All session bindings cleared');\n   210→\n   211→    return { ok: true };\n   212→  }\n   213→\n   214→  /**\n   215→   * Wait for any pending persistence operation to complete.\n   216→   * Also waits for initialization if it's in progress.\n   217→   * Useful for tests that need to verify file contents after mutation.\n   218→   * @returns {Promise<void>}\n   219→   */\n   220→  async flush() {\n   221→    if (this.#initPromise) {\n   222→      await this.#initPromise;\n   223→    }\n   224→    await this.#lastPersistPromise;\n   225→  }\n   226→\n   227→  /**\n   228→   * Check if the service is initialized.\n   229→   * @returns {boolean}\n   230→   */\n   231→  get isInitialized() {\n   232→    return this.#initialized;\n   233→  }\n   234→\n   235→  /**\n   236→   * Ensure initialization is complete (awaits pending init).\n   237→   * Use this in async contexts to guarantee the service is ready.\n   238→   * @returns {Promise<void>}\n   239→   */\n   240→  async ensureReady() {\n   241→    await this.#ensureInitialized();\n   242→  }\n   243→}\n   244→\n   245→/**\n   246→ * Factory function to create and auto-initialize a SessionBindingService instance.\n   247→ * Matches the import pattern expected by server.js.\n   248→ *\n   249→ * The returned service starts initialization immediately. Callers must\n   250→ * await service.ensureReady() or service.init() before calling synchronous\n   251→ * methods (bindSession, getBoundChatId, etc.) in async contexts.\n   252→ *\n   253→ * @param {Object} [options]\n   254→ * @param {string} [options.bindingsPath] - Full path to the bindings JSON file.\n   255→ *   If provided, persistenceDir is derived from its directory.\n   256→ * @param {string} [options.persistenceDir] - Directory for persistence (used if bindingsPath not provided).\n   257→ * @returns {SessionBindingService} A SessionBindingService instance with init in progress\n   258→ */\n   259→export function createSessionBindService({ bindingsPath, persistenceDir } = {}) {\n   260→  const opts = {};\n   261→  if (bindingsPath) {\n   262→    opts.persistenceDir = path.dirname(bindingsPath);\n   263→  } else if (persistenceDir) {\n   264→    opts.persistenceDir = persistenceDir;\n   265→  }\n   266→\n   267→  const service = new SessionBindingService(opts);\n   268→\n   269→  // Start initialization immediately\n   270→  service.init().catch((err) => {\n   271→    logger.error({ err: err.message }, 'Failed to auto-initialize SessionBindingService');\n   272→  });\n   273→\n   274→  return service;\n   275→}\n   276→\n   277→export const sessionBindingService = new SessionBindingService();\n   278→export { SessionBindingService };\n   279→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01YQWojDuu9hhr9G6EMSopGA","session_id":"1825d45b-0e87-4048-aee3-8c65afe6c801","uuid":"d6e8c41c-2e2b-43be-a86b-3db68522ae73","timestamp":"2026-03-22T06:45:24.902Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01WkVhVcN71jB7GJ9hzQj3oA","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import express from 'express';\n     2→import { config } from '../config.js';\n     3→import { createApiRouter } from '../routes/api-routes.js';\n     4→import { realtimeHub } from '../services/realtime-hub.js';\n     5→import { sessionStore } from '../services/session-store.js';\n     6→import { createSessionBindService } from '../services/session-bind.js';\n     7→import { createMessageRouter } from '../services/message-router.js';\n     8→import { executeAiCli } from '../services/ai-cli-service.js';\n     9→\n    10→export function createHttpServer({ logger, sessionBindingsPath } = {}) {\n    11→  const app = express();\n    12→\n    13→  // Initialize F-018 services\n    14→  const effectiveBindingsPath = sessionBindingsPath || config.sessionBindingsPath;\n    15→  const sessionBind = createSessionBindService({ bindingsPath: effectiveBindingsPath });\n    16→  const messageRouter = createMessageRouter({\n    17→    aiCliExecutor: executeAiCli,\n    18→    sessionStore,\n    19→    realtimeHub\n    20→  });\n    21→\n    22→  app.use(express.json({ limit: '2mb' }));\n    23→\n    24→  app.get('/healthz', (_req, res) => {\n    25→    res.json({ ok: true });\n    26→  });\n    27→\n    28→  app.use('/api', createApiRouter({ realtimeHub, sessionBind, messageRouter, sessionStore }));\n    29→  app.use(express.static('public'));\n    30→\n    31→  app.use((error, _req, res, _next) => {\n    32→    const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n    33→    logger.error({ err: message }, 'HTTP request failed');\n    34→    res.status(400).json({ ok: false, error: message });\n    35→  });\n    36→\n    37→  return app;\n    38→}\n    39→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01YQWojDuu9hhr9G6EMSopGA","session_id":"1825d45b-0e87-4048-aee3-8c65afe6c801","uuid":"e418df12-cdcd-4a7a-9353-891a7c5a7bdd","timestamp":"2026-03-22T06:45:24.905Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01HFt6tv45GcsTZCRcqWBM9S","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import { Router } from 'express';\n     2→import { buildSessionContext, resetSession } from '../services/chat-service.js';\n     3→import { captureScreenshot } from '../services/screenshot-service.js';\n     4→import { executeSystemCommand } from '../services/system-exec-service.js';\n     5→\n     6→function writeSseEvent(res, event, payload) {\n     7→  res.write(`event: ${event}\\n`);\n     8→  res.write(`data: ${JSON.stringify(payload)}\\n\\n`);\n     9→}\n    10→\n    11→export function createApiRouter({ realtimeHub, sessionBind, messageRouter, sessionStore }) {\n    12→  const router = Router();\n    13→\n    14→  // F-018: Session binding endpoints\n    15→  router.post('/bind', async (req, res, next) => {\n    16→    try {\n    17→      await sessionBind.ensureReady();\n    18→      const { webSessionId, telegramChatId } = req.body ?? {};\n    19→\n    20→      if (!webSessionId || !telegramChatId) {\n    21→        return res.status(400).json({ ok: false, error: 'webSessionId and telegramChatId are required' });\n    22→      }\n    23→\n    24→      sessionBind.bindSession(webSessionId, telegramChatId);\n    25→\n    26→      res.json({ ok: true });\n    27→    } catch (error) {\n    28→      next(error);\n    29→    }\n    30→  });\n    31→\n    32→  router.post('/unbind', async (req, res, next) => {\n    33→    try {\n    34→      await sessionBind.ensureReady();\n    35→      const { webSessionId } = req.body ?? {};\n    36→\n    37→      if (!webSessionId) {\n    38→        return res.status(400).json({ ok: false, error: 'webSessionId is required' });\n    39→      }\n    40→\n    41→      sessionBind.unbindSession(webSessionId);\n    42→\n    43→      res.json({ ok: true });\n    44→    } catch (error) {\n    45→      next(error);\n    46→    }\n    47→  });\n    48→\n    49→  router.get('/bindings', async (req, res, next) => {\n    50→    try {\n    51→      await sessionBind.ensureReady();\n    52→      const { webSessionId } = req.query;\n    53→\n    54→      if (webSessionId) {\n    55→        const telegramChatId = sessionBind.getBoundChatId(webSessionId);\n    56→        res.json({ ok: true, telegramChatId });\n    57→      } else {\n    58→        const allBindings = sessionBind.getAllBindings();\n    59→        res.json({ ok: true, bindings: allBindings });\n    60→      }\n    61→    } catch (error) {\n    62→      next(error);\n    63→    }\n    64→  });\n    65→\n    66→  // SSE events endpoint - support Telegram-bound sessions\n    67→  router.get('/events', (req, res, next) => {\n    68→    try {\n    69→      const { channel = 'web', sessionId, telegramChatId } = req.query;\n    70→\n    71→      let sessionKey;\n    72→      if (telegramChatId) {\n    73→        sessionKey = `telegram:${telegramChatId}`;\n    74→      } else {\n    75→        const session = buildSessionContext(channel, sessionId);\n    76→        sessionKey = session.sessionKey;\n    77→      }\n    78→\n    79→      res.setHeader('Content-Type', 'text/event-stream');\n    80→      res.setHeader('Cache-Control', 'no-cache');\n    81→      res.setHeader('Connection', 'keep-alive');\n    82→      res.flushHeaders?.();\n    83→\n    84→      writeSseEvent(res, 'connected', {\n    85→        ok: true,\n    86→        channel,\n    87→        sessionId,\n    88→        sessionKey\n    89→      });\n    90→\n    91→      // F-018: Replay message history for offline clients (T4.2)\n    92→      const existingMessages = sessionStore.get(sessionKey);\n    93→      for (const msg of existingMessages) {\n    94→        writeSseEvent(res, msg.role === 'user' ? 'user_message' : 'assistant_message', {\n    95→          role: msg.role,\n    96→          content: msg.content,\n    97→          replay: true\n    98→        });\n    99→      }\n   100→\n   101→      const unsubscribe = realtimeHub.subscribe(sessionKey, (event) => {\n   102→        writeSseEvent(res, event.type, event.payload);\n   103→      });\n   104→\n   105→      const heartbeat = setInterval(() => {\n   106→        res.write(': ping\\n\\n');\n   107→      }, 20000);\n   108→\n   109→      req.on('close', () => {\n   110→        clearInterval(heartbeat);\n   111→        unsubscribe();\n   112→      });\n   113→    } catch (error) {\n   114→      next(error);\n   115→    }\n   116→  });\n   117→\n   118→  // F-018: Modified /api/chat to use message-router and support Telegram binding\n   119→  router.post('/chat', async (req, res, next) => {\n   120→    try {\n   121→      await sessionBind.ensureReady();\n   122→      const { channel = 'web', sessionId, message, telegramChatId } = req.body ?? {};\n   123→\n   124→      let effectiveTelegramChatId = telegramChatId;\n   125→\n   126→      // If no telegramChatId provided but session is bound, use the bound chat ID\n   127→      if (!effectiveTelegramChatId) {\n   128→        effectiveTelegramChatId = sessionBind.getBoundChatId(sessionId);\n   129→      }\n   130→\n   131→      const result = await messageRouter.processMessage({\n   132→        channel,\n   133→        sessionId,\n   134→        message,\n   135→        telegramChatId: effectiveTelegramChatId,\n   136→        hooks: {\n   137→          onStatus: (payload) => {\n   138→            // Status events are already published by message-router\n   139→          },\n   140→          onAssistantChunk: (data) => {\n   141→            // Chunk events are already published by message-router\n   142→          },\n   143→          onAssistantDone: (data) => {\n   144→            // Done events are already published by message-router\n   145→          }\n   146→        }\n   147→      });\n   148→\n   149→      res.json({ ok: true, reply: result.reply });\n   150→    } catch (error) {\n   151→      next(error);\n   152→    }\n   153→  });\n   154→\n   155→  router.post('/chat/reset', async (req, res, next) => {\n   156→    try {\n   157→      await sessionBind.ensureReady();\n   158→      const { channel = 'web', sessionId, telegramChatId } = req.body ?? {};\n   159→\n   160→      let sessionKey;\n   161→      let effectiveTelegramChatId;\n   162→\n   163→      if (telegramChatId) {\n   164→        sessionKey = `telegram:${telegramChatId}`;\n   165→      } else if (channel === 'web' && sessionId) {\n   166→        effectiveTelegramChatId = sessionBind.getBoundChatId(sessionId);\n   167→        if (effectiveTelegramChatId) {\n   168→          sessionKey = `telegram:${effectiveTelegramChatId}`;\n   169→        } else {\n   170→          resetSession({ channel, sessionId });\n   171→          return res.json({ ok: true });\n   172→        }\n   173→      } else {\n   174→        resetSession({ channel, sessionId });\n   175→        return res.json({ ok: true });\n   176→      }\n   177→\n   178→      sessionStore.clear(sessionKey);\n   179→      res.json({ ok: true });\n   180→    } catch (error) {\n   181→      next(error);\n   182→    }\n   183→  });\n   184→\n   185→  router.post('/screenshot', async (_req, res, next) => {\n   186→    try {\n   187→      const { mimeType, imageBase64 } = await captureScreenshot();\n   188→      res.json({ ok: true, mimeType, imageBase64 });\n   189→    } catch (error) {\n   190→      next(error);\n   191→    }\n   192→  });\n   193→\n   194→  router.post('/system/exec', async (req, res, next) => {\n   195→    try {\n   196→      const { command } = req.body ?? {};\n   197→      const result = await executeSystemCommand(command);\n   198→      res.json({ ok: true, ...result });\n   199→    } catch (error) {\n   200→      next(error);\n   201→    }\n   202→  });\n   203→\n   204→  return router;\n   205→}\n   206→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01YQWojDuu9hhr9G6EMSopGA","session_id":"1825d45b-0e87-4048-aee3-8c65afe6c801","uuid":"6bbd8db8-e439-49c2-a983-4d6e6a8eab92","timestamp":"2026-03-22T06:45:24.906Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01J5xLyL1oTVZB4LEVwhX6yk","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * Message Router Service\n     3→ *\n     4→ * Unified message processor for both Web and Telegram channels.\n     5→ * Routes messages through ai-cli-service and publishes events via realtime-hub.\n     6→ *\n     7→ * F-018: Web-Telegram Bidirectional Sync\n     8→ */\n     9→\n    10→import { sanitizeInput } from '../security/guard.js';\n    11→import { logger } from '../utils/logger.js';\n    12→import { chatQueue } from './chat-queue.js';\n    13→\n    14→/**\n    15→ * @typedef {Object} MessageProcessOptions\n    16→ * @property {string} channel - Channel name ('web' or 'telegram')\n    17→ * @property {string} sessionId - Session ID (web session ID or Telegram chat ID)\n    18→ * @property {string} message - User message\n    19→ * @property {string} [telegramChatId] - Bound Telegram chat ID (optional)\n    20→ * @property {string} [userId] - User ID who initiated the message\n    21→ * @property {Object} [hooks] - Callback hooks\n    22→ * @property {Function} [hooks.onStatus] - Status change callback (payload) => void\n    23→ * @property {Function} [hooks.onAssistantChunk] - Chunk callback (data) => void\n    24→ * @property {Function} [hooks.onAssistantDone] - Done callback (data) => void\n    25→ */\n    26→\n    27→/**\n    28→ * Creates a message router instance\n    29→ * @param {Object} dependencies\n    30→ * @param {Function} dependencies.aiCliExecutor - AI CLI executor (executeAiCli function)\n    31→ * @param {Object} dependencies.sessionStore - Session store instance\n    32→ * @param {Object} dependencies.realtimeHub - Realtime hub instance\n    33→ * @returns {MessageRouter}\n    34→ */\n    35→export function createMessageRouter({ aiCliExecutor, sessionStore, realtimeHub }) {\n    36→  return {\n    37→    /**\n    38→     * Process a message from any channel\n    39→     * @param {MessageProcessOptions} options\n    40→     * @returns {Promise<{reply: string}>}\n    41→     */\n    42→    async processMessage(options) {\n    43→      const {\n    44→        channel,\n    45→        sessionId,\n    46→        message,\n    47→        telegramChatId,\n    48→        userId,\n    49→        hooks = {}\n    50→      } = options;\n    51→\n    52→      // Validate required fields\n    53→      const normalizedChannel = String(channel ?? '').trim();\n    54→      const normalizedSessionId = String(sessionId ?? '').trim();\n    55→      const normalizedMessage = String(message ?? '').trim();\n    56→\n    57→      if (!normalizedSessionId) {\n    58→        throw new Error('sessionId 不能为空。');\n    59→      }\n    60→\n    61→      if (!normalizedMessage) {\n    62→        throw new Error('message 不能为空。');\n    63→      }\n    64→\n    65→      // Determine session key based on binding\n    66→      let sessionKey;\n    67→      if (telegramChatId) {\n    68→        sessionKey = `telegram:${telegramChatId}`;\n    69→      } else {\n    70→        sessionKey = `${normalizedChannel}:${normalizedSessionId}`;\n    71→      }\n    72→\n    73→      // Use chat queue to ensure sequential processing per session\n    74→      return chatQueue.run(sessionKey, async () => {\n    75→        const sanitized = sanitizeInput(normalizedMessage);\n    76→\n    77→        // Publish accepted status\n    78→        hooks.onStatus?.({ stage: 'accepted', channel: normalizedChannel, sessionId: normalizedSessionId, telegramChatId });\n    79→        realtimeHub.publish(sessionKey, { type: 'status', payload: { stage: 'accepted', channel: normalizedChannel, sessionId: normalizedSessionId, telegramChatId } });\n    80→\n    81→        // Append user message to session store\n    82→        sessionStore.append(sessionKey, 'user', sanitized);\n    83→\n    84→        // Publish user message event for cross-channel sync\n    85→        realtimeHub.publish(sessionKey, { type: 'user_message', payload: { channel: normalizedChannel, sessionId: normalizedSessionId, message: sanitized, timestamp: Date.now() } });\n    86→\n    87→        // Build prompt for AI CLI\n    88→        const prompt = sessionStore.toPrompt(sessionKey, normalizedChannel);\n    89→\n    90→        // Publish running status\n    91→        hooks.onStatus?.({ stage: 'running', channel: normalizedChannel, sessionId: normalizedSessionId, telegramChatId });\n    92→        realtimeHub.publish(sessionKey, { type: 'status', payload: { stage: 'running', channel: normalizedChannel, sessionId: normalizedSessionId, telegramChatId } });\n    93→\n    94→        logger.info({ sessionKey, channel: normalizedChannel, userId }, 'Processing message');\n    95→\n    96→        // Execute via AI CLI service\n    97→        const result = await aiCliExecutor({\n    98→          sessionId: sessionKey,\n    99→          prompt,\n   100→          userId,\n   101→          hooks: {\n   102→            onChunk: (text) => {\n   103→              // Forward chunks to caller and realtime hub\n   104→              hooks.onAssistantChunk?.({ text, channel: normalizedChannel, sessionId: normalizedSessionId, telegramChatId });\n   105→              realtimeHub.publish(sessionKey, { type: 'assistant_chunk', payload: { text, channel: normalizedChannel, sessionId: normalizedSessionId, telegramChatId } });\n   106→            },\n   107→            onStatus: (status) => {\n   108→              logger.debug({ sessionKey, status }, 'AI CLI status changed');\n   109→            }\n   110→          }\n   111→        });\n   112→\n   113→        // Append assistant reply to session store\n   114→        sessionStore.append(sessionKey, 'assistant', result.output);\n   115→\n   116→        // Publish assistant done event\n   117→        const donePayload = { reply: result.output, channel: normalizedChannel, sessionId: normalizedSessionId, telegramChatId };\n   118→        hooks.onAssistantDone?.(donePayload);\n   119→        realtimeHub.publish(sessionKey, { type: 'assistant_done', payload: { ...donePayload, timestamp: Date.now() } });\n   120→\n   121→        logger.info({ sessionKey, elapsedMs: result.elapsedMs }, 'Message processed');\n   122→\n   123→        return { reply: result.output };\n   124→      });\n   125→    }\n   126→  };\n   127→}\n   128→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01YQWojDuu9hhr9G6EMSopGA","session_id":"1825d45b-0e87-4048-aee3-8c65afe6c801","uuid":"af46de65-042f-4d54-a603-77e8dafbb364","timestamp":"2026-03-22T06:45:24.908Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_013oTJX94vWkvUE75ngut3DW","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * Services Index\n     3→ * Exports all service modules for convenience.\n     4→ */\n     5→\n     6→// F-005: Pipeline Status Aggregation and Log Streaming\n     7→export { createStatusAggregator } from './status-aggregator.js';\n     8→export { createLogPager } from './log-pager.js';\n     9→export { createTelegramPusher } from './telegram-pusher.js';\n    10→\n    11→// Existing services\n    12→export { chatQueue } from './chat-queue.js';\n    13→export { chatWithSession, buildSessionContext, resetSession } from './chat-service.js';\n    14→export { captureScreenshot } from './screenshot-service.js';\n    15→export { executeSystemCommand } from './system-exec-service.js';\n    16→export { realtimeHub } from './realtime-hub.js';\n    17→export { sessionStore } from './session-store.js';\n    18→export { createPipelineControlService } from './pipeline-control-service.js';\n    19→export { createPlanIngestionService } from './plan-ingestion-service.js';\n    20→export {\n    21→  createPipelineController,\n    22→  getDefaultPipelineController,\n    23→  startPipeline,\n    24→  stopPipeline,\n    25→  retryTarget,\n    26→  runSingle,\n    27→  getStatus,\n    28→  getLogs,\n    29→  forceUnlock\n    30→} from './pipeline-controller.js';\n    31→\n    32→// F-006: Safety and Permission Guard - Audit Log Service\n    33→export {\n    34→  initAuditLogService,\n    35→  logAuditEntry,\n    36→  queryAuditLogs,\n    37→  resetAuditLogService,\n    38→  getAuditLogStats\n    39→} from './audit-log-service.js';\n    40→\n    41→// F-011: AI CLI Proxy\n    42→export {\n    43→  executeAiCli,\n    44→  interruptAiCli,\n    45→  isAiCliRunning,\n    46→  getActiveProcessInfo,\n    47→  canInterruptAiCli,\n    48→  getMetrics,\n    49→  resetMetrics\n    50→} from './ai-cli-service.js';\n    51→\n    52→// F-013: Session and Context Manager\n    53→export { sessionContextService } from './session-context-service.js';\n    54→export { aliasStore } from './alias-store.js';\n    55→\n    56→// F-014: Notification and Scheduled Tasks\n    57→export { scheduledTaskService } from './scheduled-task-service.js';\n    58→export { fileWatcherService } from './file-watcher-service.js';\n    59→\n    60→// F-018: Web-Telegram Bidirectional Sync\n    61→export { createSessionBindService } from './session-bind.js';\n    62→export { createMessageRouter } from './message-router.js';\n    63→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01YQWojDuu9hhr9G6EMSopGA","session_id":"1825d45b-0e87-4048-aee3-8c65afe6c801","uuid":"7941dead-1862-4d91-8f1a-9f959730cfb4","timestamp":"2026-03-22T06:45:24.909Z"}
{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01BfkQ7Q4nQ9Rau8ebgF9S7K","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→import { Telegraf } from 'telegraf';\n     2→import { createReadStream } from 'node:fs';\n     3→import { access, stat } from 'node:fs/promises';\n     4→import os from 'node:os';\n     5→import path from 'node:path';\n     6→import { config } from '../config.js';\n     7→import { logger } from '../utils/logger.js';\n     8→import { isAllowedUser } from '../security/guard.js';\n     9→import { chatWithSession, resetSession } from '../services/chat-service.js';\n    10→import { executeAiCli, interruptAiCli, isAiCliRunning } from '../services/ai-cli-service.js';\n    11→import { createMessageRouter } from '../services/message-router.js';\n    12→import { realtimeHub } from '../services/realtime-hub.js';\n    13→import { createSessionBindService } from '../services/session-bind.js';\n    14→import { captureScreenshot } from '../services/screenshot-service.js';\n    15→import { executeCommand, confirmHighRiskCommand } from '../services/command-executor-service.js';\n    16→import { createPlanIngestionService } from '../services/plan-ingestion-service.js';\n    17→import { loadPipelineInfraConfig } from '../pipeline-infra/config-loader.js';\n    18→import { registerCommand } from './commands/index.js';\n    19→import { routeCommand } from './commands/index.js';\n    20→import { pipelineMeta, handlePipeline } from './commands/handlers/pipeline.js';\n    21→import { bugfixMeta, handleBugfix } from './commands/handlers/bugfix.js';\n    22→import { plannerMeta, handlePlanner } from './commands/handlers/planner.js';\n    23→import { statusMeta, handleStatus } from './commands/handlers/status.js';\n    24→import { logsMeta, handleLogs } from './commands/handlers/logs.js';\n    25→import { stopMeta, handleStop } from './commands/handlers/stop.js';\n    26→import { planMeta, handlePlan } from './commands/handlers/plan.js';\n    27→import { auditMeta, handleAudit } from './commands/handlers/audit.js';\n    28→import { commitMeta, handleCommit } from './commands/handlers/commit.js';\n    29→import { commitsMeta, handleCommits } from './commands/handlers/commits.js';\n    30→// F-009: New command handlers\n    31→import { cdMeta, handleCd } from './commands/handlers/cd.js';\n    32→import { moreMeta, handleMore } from './commands/handlers/more.js';\n    33→// F-010: File Manager command handlers\n    34→import { lsMeta, handleLs } from './commands/handlers/ls.js';\n    35→import { treeMeta, handleTree } from './commands/handlers/tree.js';\n    36→import { catMeta, handleCat } from './commands/handlers/cat.js';\n    37→import { headMeta, handleHead } from './commands/handlers/head.js';\n    38→import { tailMeta, handleTail } from './commands/handlers/tail.js';\n    39→import { findMeta, handleFind } from './commands/handlers/find.js';\n    40→import { uploadMeta, handleUpload } from './commands/handlers/upload.js';\n    41→import { downloadMeta, handleDownload } from './commands/handlers/download.js';\n    42→// F-012: System Monitor command handlers\n    43→import { sysinfoMeta, handleSysinfo } from './commands/handlers/sysinfo.js';\n    44→import { psMeta, handlePs } from './commands/handlers/ps.js';\n    45→import { killMeta, handleKill } from './commands/handlers/kill.js';\n    46→import { monitorMeta, handleMonitor } from './commands/handlers/monitor.js';\n    47→// F-013: Session and Context Manager command handlers\n    48→import { historyMeta, handleHistory } from './commands/handlers/history.js';\n    49→import { aliasMeta, handleAlias } from './commands/handlers/alias.js';\n    50→import { sessionsMeta, handleSessions } from './commands/handlers/sessions.js';\n    51→// F-014: Notification and Scheduled Tasks command handlers\n    52→import { cronMeta, handleCron } from './commands/handlers/cron.js';\n    53→import { jobsMeta, handleJobs } from './commands/handlers/jobs.js';\n    54→import { watchMeta, handleWatch } from './commands/handlers/watch.js';\n    55→// F-015: AI CLI Backend Switcher command handler\n    56→import { cliMeta, handleCli } from './commands/handlers/cli.js';\n    57→// F-017: Runtime Config Manager command handler\n    58→import { configMeta, handleConfig } from './commands/handlers/config.js';\n    59→import { generateHelp } from './commands/help.js';\n    60→import { sessionStore } from '../services/session-store.js';\n    61→import { sessionContextService } from '../services/session-context-service.js';\n    62→import { aliasStore } from '../services/alias-store.js';\n    63→import { scheduledTaskService } from '../services/scheduled-task-service.js';\n    64→import { fileWatcherService } from '../services/file-watcher-service.js';\n    65→import { convertToMarkdownV2 } from '../utils/markdown-v2-formatter.js';\n    66→import { escapeMarkdownV2 } from '../utils/markdown-v2-formatter.js';\n    67→\n    68→const TELEGRAM_MSG_CHUNK_SIZE = 3800;\n    69→const STREAM_MIN_CHARS = 220;\n    70→const STREAM_FLUSH_INTERVAL_MS = 1200;\n    71→const TYPING_INTERVAL_MS = 3500;\n    72→const PHOTO_EXTENSIONS = new Set(['.png', '.jpg', '.jpeg', '.webp']);\n    73→const DOCUMENT_EXTENSIONS = new Set(['.pdf', '.txt', '.json', '.md', '.csv', '.log']);\n    74→const ALLOWED_FILE_EXTENSIONS = new Set([...PHOTO_EXTENSIONS, ...DOCUMENT_EXTENSIONS]);\n    75→const TELEGRAM_MAX_PHOTO_BYTES = 10 * 1024 * 1024;\n    76→const TELEGRAM_MAX_DOCUMENT_BYTES = 45 * 1024 * 1024;\n    77→const TELEGRAM_HANDLER_TIMEOUT_MS = 10 * 60 * 1000;\n    78→const TMP_DIR = path.resolve(os.tmpdir());\n    79→const HOME_DIR = path.resolve(os.homedir());\n    80→const DESKTOP_DIR = path.join(HOME_DIR, 'Desktop');\n    81→const DOWNLOADS_DIR = path.join(HOME_DIR, 'Downloads');\n    82→const DEFAULT_ALLOWED_FILE_ROOTS = [path.resolve(process.cwd()), DESKTOP_DIR, DOWNLOADS_DIR, TMP_DIR];\n    83→const DEFAULT_FILE_CANDIDATE_DIRS = [path.resolve(process.cwd()), DESKTOP_DIR, DOWNLOADS_DIR, TMP_DIR];\n    84→\n    85→function resolveConfiguredDirs(configuredDirs = [], fallbackDirs = []) {\n    86→  const normalized = configuredDirs\n    87→    .map((dir) => String(dir ?? '').trim())\n    88→    .filter(Boolean)\n    89→    .map((dir) => path.resolve(dir));\n    90→\n    91→  if (normalized.length > 0) {\n    92→    return [...new Set(normalized)];\n    93→  }\n    94→\n    95→  return [...new Set(fallbackDirs.map((dir) => path.resolve(String(dir))))];\n    96→}\n    97→\n    98→const ALLOWED_FILE_ROOTS = resolveConfiguredDirs(config.telegramFileAllowedRoots, DEFAULT_ALLOWED_FILE_ROOTS);\n    99→const FILE_CANDIDATE_DIRS = resolveConfiguredDirs(config.telegramFileCandidateDirs, DEFAULT_FILE_CANDIDATE_DIRS);\n   100→\n   101→function splitMessage(text, chunkSize = TELEGRAM_MSG_CHUNK_SIZE) {\n   102→  const chunks = [];\n   103→  for (let i = 0; i < text.length; i += chunkSize) {\n   104→    chunks.push(text.slice(i, i + chunkSize));\n   105→  }\n   106→  return chunks;\n   107→}\n   108→\n   109→function truncate(text, maxLen) {\n   110→  if (!text) return '';\n   111→  if (text.length <= maxLen) return text;\n   112→  return text.substring(0, maxLen) + '...';\n   113→}\n   114→\n   115→function sanitizeMarkerPath(raw) {\n   116→  return String(raw ?? '')\n   117→    .trim()\n   118→    .replace(/^['\"`]+/, '')\n   119→    .replace(/['\"`]+$/, '');\n   120→}\n   121→\n   122→function extractFileMarkers(text = '') {\n   123→  const fileRefs = [];\n   124→\n   125→  const withSendFileRemoved = text.replace(\n   126→    /(?:^|\\n)\\s*(?:[-*]\\s*)?`?SEND_FILE:([^\\n`]+)`?\\s*(?=\\n|$)/g,\n   127→    (_full, rawRef) => {\n   128→      const ref = sanitizeMarkerPath(rawRef);\n   129→      if (ref) {\n   130→        fileRefs.push(ref);\n   131→      }\n   132→      return '\\n';\n   133→    }\n   134→  );\n   135→\n   136→  const withImageRemoved = withSendFileRemoved.replace(/@image:([^\\s`]+)/g, (_full, rawRef) => {\n   137→    const ref = sanitizeMarkerPath(rawRef);\n   138→    if (ref) {\n   139→      fileRefs.push(ref);\n   140→    }\n   141→    return '';\n   142→  });\n   143→\n   144→  const withBacktickPathRemoved = withImageRemoved.replace(\n   145→    /`((?:\\/[^`\\n\\r]+)+\\.(?:png|jpg|jpeg|webp|pdf|txt|json|md|csv|log))`/gi,\n   146→    (_full, rawRef) => {\n   147→      const ref = sanitizeMarkerPath(rawRef);\n   148→      if (ref) {\n   149→        fileRefs.push(ref);\n   150→      }\n   151→      return '';\n   152→    }\n   153→  );\n   154→\n   155→  const withLabeledPathRemoved = withBacktickPathRemoved.replace(\n   156→    /(?:文件路径|path)\\s*[:：]\\s*((?:\\/[^\\n`\\r]+)+\\.(?:png|jpg|jpeg|webp|pdf|txt|json|md|csv|log))/gi,\n   157→    (_full, rawRef) => {\n   158→      const ref = sanitizeMarkerPath(rawRef);\n   159→      if (ref) {\n   160→        fileRefs.push(ref);\n   161→      }\n   162→      return '';\n   163→    }\n   164→  );\n   165→\n   166→  const withAbsolutePathLineRemoved = withLabeledPathRemoved.replace(\n   167→    /(?:^|\\n)\\s*(?:[-*]\\s*)?((?:\\/[^\\n`\\r]+)+\\.(?:png|jpg|jpeg|webp|pdf|txt|json|md|csv|log))\\s*(?=\\n|$)/gi,\n   168→    (_full, rawRef) => {\n   169→      const ref = sanitizeMarkerPath(rawRef);\n   170→      if (ref) {\n   171→        fileRefs.push(ref);\n   172→      }\n   173→      return '\\n';\n   174→    }\n   175→  );\n   176→\n   177→  return {\n   178→    fileRefs: [...new Set(fileRefs)],\n   179→    cleanedText: withAbsolutePathLineRemoved.replace(/\\n{3,}/g, '\\n\\n').trim()\n   180→  };\n   181→}\n   182→\n   183→function isPathWithinRoot(targetPath, rootPath) {\n   184→  const relative = path.relative(rootPath, targetPath);\n   185→  return relative === '' || (!relative.startsWith('..') && !path.isAbsolute(relative));\n   186→}\n   187→\n   188→function isAllowedFilePath(filePath) {\n   189→  const resolved = path.resolve(filePath);\n   190→  return ALLOWED_FILE_ROOTS.some((root) => isPathWithinRoot(resolved, root));\n   191→}\n   192→\n   193→function buildFileCandidates(normalizedPath) {\n   194→  if (path.isAbsolute(normalizedPath)) {\n   195→    return [normalizedPath];\n   196→  }\n   197→\n   198→  const baseName = path.basename(normalizedPath);\n   199→  const candidates = [\n   200→    path.resolve(process.cwd(), normalizedPath),\n   201→    ...FILE_CANDIDATE_DIRS.map((dir) => path.resolve(dir, baseName))\n   202→  ];\n   203→\n   204→  return [...new Set(candidates)];\n   205→}\n   206→\n   207→async function resolveLocalFilePath(fileRef) {\n   208→  const normalized = sanitizeMarkerPath(fileRef);\n   209→  if (!normalized) {\n   210→    return { filePath: null, triedPaths: [], rejectReason: 'empty_path' };\n   211→  }\n   212→\n   213→  if (!path.isAbsolute(normalized)) {\n   214→    return { filePath: null, triedPaths: [], rejectReason: 'relative_path_not_allowed' };\n   215→  }\n   216→\n   217→  const candidates = buildFileCandidates(normalized);\n   218→\n   219→  for (const candidate of candidates) {\n   220→    try {\n   221→      await access(candidate);\n   222→      return { filePath: candidate, triedPaths: candidates };\n   223→    } catch {\n   224→      // ignore\n   225→    }\n   226→  }\n   227→\n   228→  return { filePath: null, triedPaths: candidates, rejectReason: 'not_found' };\n   229→}\n   230→\n   231→async function validateFileForTelegram(filePath) {\n   232→  const resolvedPath = path.resolve(filePath);\n   233→  if (!isAllowedFilePath(resolvedPath)) {\n   234→    return { ok: false, reason: `路径不在允许范围：${resolvedPath}` };\n   235→  }\n   236→\n   237→  const ext = path.extname(resolvedPath).toLowerCase();\n   238→  if (!ALLOWED_FILE_EXTENSIONS.has(ext)) {\n   239→    return { ok: false, reason: `不支持的文件类型：${ext || '(unknown)'}` };\n   240→  }\n   241→\n   242→  const fileStat = await stat(resolvedPath);\n   243→  const isPhoto = PHOTO_EXTENSIONS.has(ext);\n   244→  const maxSize = isPhoto ? TELEGRAM_MAX_PHOTO_BYTES : TELEGRAM_MAX_DOCUMENT_BYTES;\n   245→\n   246→  if (fileStat.size > maxSize) {\n   247→    return {\n   248→      ok: false,\n   249→      reason: `文件过大：${Math.ceil(fileStat.size / 1024 / 1024)}MB，限制 ${Math.floor(maxSize / 1024 / 1024)}MB`\n   250→    };\n   251→  }\n   252→\n   253→  return { ok: true, isPhoto, resolvedPath };\n   254→}\n   255→\n   256→function isTimeoutLikeError(message = '') {\n   257→  const normalized = String(message).toLowerCase();\n   258→  return normalized.includes('timed out') || normalized.includes('etimedout') || normalized.includes('timeout');\n   259→}\n   260→\n   261→function sleep(ms) {\n   262→  return new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, ms));\n   263→}\n   264→\n   265→async function sendTelegramFileByType(ctx, filePath, isPhoto) {\n   266→  if (isPhoto) {\n   267→    await ctx.replyWithPhoto({ source: createReadStream(filePath) }, { caption: path.basename(filePath) });\n   268→    return;\n   269→  }\n   270→\n   271→  await ctx.replyWithDocument({ source: createReadStream(filePath), filename: path.basename(filePath) });\n   272→}\n   273→\n   274→async function replyFiles(ctx, fileRefs = []) {\n   275→  const results = [];\n   276→\n   277→  for (const fileRef of fileRefs) {\n   278→    const { filePath, triedPaths, rejectReason } = await resolveLocalFilePath(fileRef);\n   279→    if (!filePath) {\n   280→      const reason = rejectReason || 'not_found';\n   281→      results.push({ fileRef, sent: false, reason, triedPaths });\n   282→      logger.warn({ fileRef, reason, triedPaths }, 'File unavailable for telegram upload');\n   283→      continue;\n   284→    }\n   285→\n   286→    try {\n   287→      const validation = await validateFileForTelegram(filePath);\n   288→      if (!validation.ok) {\n   289→        results.push({ fileRef, sent: false, reason: validation.reason, filePath, triedPaths });\n   290→        logger.warn({ fileRef, filePath, reason: validation.reason }, 'File validation failed for telegram upload');\n   291→        continue;\n   292→      }\n   293→\n   294→      const actualPath = validation.resolvedPath;\n   295→      let sent = false;\n   296→      let lastReason = '';\n   297→\n   298→      for (let attempt = 1; attempt <= 2; attempt += 1) {\n   299→        try {\n   300→          await sendTelegramFileByType(ctx, actualPath, validation.isPhoto);\n   301→          sent = true;\n   302→          logger.info(\n   303→            { fileRef, filePath: actualPath, as: validation.isPhoto ? 'photo' : 'document', attempt },\n   304→            'Telegram file sent'\n   305→          );\n   306→          break;\n   307→        } catch (error) {\n   308→          lastReason = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n   309→          logger.warn(\n   310→            { fileRef, filePath: actualPath, err: lastReason, attempt },\n   311→            'Telegram file send attempt failed'\n   312→          );\n   313→\n   314→          if (attempt < 2 && isTimeoutLikeError(lastReason)) {\n   315→            await sleep(600);\n   316→            continue;\n   317→          }\n   318→\n   319→          break;\n   320→        }\n   321→      }\n   322→\n   323→      if (!sent) {\n   324→        results.push({ fileRef, sent: false, reason: lastReason || 'unknown_error', filePath: actualPath, triedPaths });\n   325→        logger.error({ fileRef, filePath: actualPath, err: lastReason }, 'Failed to send file to telegram');\n   326→        continue;\n   327→      }\n   328→\n   329→      results.push({ fileRef, sent: true, filePath: actualPath, triedPaths });\n   330→    } catch (error) {\n   331→      const reason = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n   332→      results.push({ fileRef, sent: false, reason, filePath, triedPaths });\n   333→      logger.error({ fileRef, filePath, err: reason }, 'Failed to send file to telegram');\n   334→    }\n   335→  }\n   336→\n   337→  return results;\n   338→}\n   339→\n   340→async function safeReply(ctx, text) {\n   341→  try {\n   342→    await ctx.reply(text);\n   343→    return true;\n   344→  } catch (error) {\n   345→    const reason = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n   346→    logger.error({ err: reason }, 'Failed to send telegram text reply');\n   347→    return false;\n   348→  }\n   349→}\n   350→\n   351→async function replyLargeText(ctx, text) {\n   352→  const chunks = splitMessage(text);\n   353→  for (const chunk of chunks) {\n   354→    const ok = await safeReply(ctx, chunk);\n   355→    if (!ok) {\n   356→      break;\n   357→    }\n   358→  }\n   359→}\n   360→\n   361→async function safeEditMessageText(ctx, messageId, text) {\n   362→  const nextText = text && text.trim() ? text : ' ';\n   363→\n   364→  try {\n   365→    await ctx.telegram.editMessageText(ctx.chat.id, messageId, undefined, nextText);\n   366→  } catch (error) {\n   367→    const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n   368→    if (message.includes('message is not modified')) {\n   369→      return;\n   370→    }\n   371→    throw error;\n   372→  }\n   373→}\n   374→\n   375→function createEditableStreamPublisher(ctx) {\n   376→  let fullText = '';\n   377→  let renderedText = '';\n   378→  let pendingChars = 0;\n   379→  let lastFlushAt = 0;\n   380→  let flushChain = Promise.resolve();\n   381→  let activeMessage = null;\n   382→  let activeSegmentIndex = 0;\n   383→  let publishedMessageCount = 0;\n   384→\n   385→  async function ensureActiveMessage() {\n   386→    if (activeMessage) {\n   387→      return;\n   388→    }\n   389→    activeMessage = await ctx.reply('处理中...');\n   390→    activeSegmentIndex = 0;\n   391→    publishedMessageCount += 1;\n   392→  }\n   393→\n   394→  async function render(force = false) {\n   395→    const now = Date.now();\n   396→\n   397→    if (!force && pendingChars < STREAM_MIN_CHARS && now - lastFlushAt < STREAM_FLUSH_INTERVAL_MS) {\n   398→      return;\n   399→    }\n   400→\n   401→    if (fullText === renderedText) {\n   402→      pendingChars = 0;\n   403→      return;\n   404→    }\n   405→\n   406→    await ensureActiveMessage();\n   407→\n   408→    const segments = splitMessage(fullText);\n   409→    const targetLastIndex = Math.max(segments.length - 1, 0);\n   410→\n   411→    while (activeSegmentIndex < targetLastIndex) {\n   412→      const text = segments[activeSegmentIndex] ?? ' ';\n   413→      await safeEditMessageText(ctx, activeMessage.message_id, text);\n   414→\n   415→      activeMessage = await ctx.reply('继续输出中...');\n   416→      activeSegmentIndex += 1;\n   417→      publishedMessageCount += 1;\n   418→    }\n   419→\n   420→    const activeText = segments[targetLastIndex] ?? ' ';\n   421→    await safeEditMessageText(ctx, activeMessage.message_id, activeText);\n   422→\n   423→    renderedText = fullText;\n   424→    pendingChars = 0;\n   425→    lastFlushAt = now;\n   426→  }\n   427→\n   428→  function enqueueRender(force = false) {\n   429→    flushChain = flushChain.then(() => render(force));\n   430→  }\n   431→\n   432→  return {\n   433→    push(text) {\n   434→      const appendText = text ?? '';\n   435→      if (!appendText) {\n   436→        return;\n   437→      }\n   438→      fullText += appendText;\n   439→      pendingChars += appendText.length;\n   440→      enqueueRender(false);\n   441→    },\n   442→    setFinalText(text) {\n   443→      fullText = text ?? '';\n   444→      pendingChars = Math.max(pendingChars, STREAM_MIN_CHARS);\n   445→      enqueueRender(true);\n   446→    },\n   447→    async finish() {\n   448→      enqueueRender(true);\n   449→      await flushChain;\n   450→      return {\n   451→        outputLength: renderedText.length,\n   452→        messageCount: publishedMessageCount\n   453→      };\n   454→    }\n   455→  };\n   456→}\n   457→\n   458→function buildSessionId(ctx) {\n   459→  return String(ctx.chat.id);\n   460→}\n   461→\n   462→function ensureAllowed(ctx) {\n   463→  const userId = ctx.from?.id;\n   464→  if (!isAllowedUser(userId)) {\n   465→    throw new Error('当前账号未被授权使用该机器人。');\n   466→  }\n   467→}\n   468→\n   469→/**\n   470→ * Register all pipeline-related commands.\n   471→ */\n   472→function registerPipelineCommands() {\n   473→  registerCommand(pipelineMeta, handlePipeline);\n   474→  registerCommand(bugfixMeta, handleBugfix);\n   475→  registerCommand(plannerMeta, handlePlanner);\n   476→  registerCommand(statusMeta, handleStatus);\n   477→  registerCommand(logsMeta, handleLogs);\n   478→  registerCommand(stopMeta, handleStop);\n   479→  registerCommand(planMeta, handlePlan);\n   480→  registerCommand(auditMeta, handleAudit);\n   481→  registerCommand(commitMeta, handleCommit);\n   482→  registerCommand(commitsMeta, handleCommits);\n   483→  // F-009: New commands\n   484→  registerCommand(cdMeta, handleCd);\n   485→  registerCommand(moreMeta, handleMore);\n   486→  // F-010: File Manager commands\n   487→  registerCommand(lsMeta, handleLs);\n   488→  registerCommand(treeMeta, handleTree);\n   489→  registerCommand(catMeta, handleCat);\n   490→  registerCommand(headMeta, handleHead);\n   491→  registerCommand(tailMeta, handleTail);\n   492→  registerCommand(findMeta, handleFind);\n   493→  registerCommand(uploadMeta, handleUpload);\n   494→  registerCommand(downloadMeta, handleDownload);\n   495→  // F-012: System Monitor commands\n   496→  registerCommand(sysinfoMeta, handleSysinfo);\n   497→  registerCommand(psMeta, handlePs);\n   498→  registerCommand(killMeta, handleKill);\n   499→  registerCommand(monitorMeta, handleMonitor);\n   500→  // F-013: Session and Context Manager commands\n   501→  registerCommand(historyMeta, handleHistory);\n   502→  registerCommand(aliasMeta, handleAlias);\n   503→  registerCommand(sessionsMeta, handleSessions);\n   504→  // F-014: Notification and Scheduled Tasks commands\n   505→  registerCommand(cronMeta, handleCron);\n   506→  registerCommand(jobsMeta, handleJobs);\n   507→  registerCommand(watchMeta, handleWatch);\n   508→  // F-015: AI CLI Backend Switcher command\n   509→  registerCommand(cliMeta, handleCli);\n   510→  // F-017: Runtime Config Manager command\n   511→  registerCommand(configMeta, handleConfig);\n   512→}\n   513→\n   514→export async function createTelegramBot() {\n   515→  const bot = new Telegraf(config.telegramBotToken, {\n   516→    handlerTimeout: TELEGRAM_HANDLER_TIMEOUT_MS\n   517→  });\n   518→\n   519→  // F-013: Initialize session context service\n   520→  await sessionContextService.initSessionContext({ dataDir: config.sessionPersistenceDir });\n   521→  await aliasStore.initAliasStore({ persistencePath: config.aliasPersistencePath });\n   522→\n   523→  // F-013: Restore sessions from disk\n   524→  await sessionContextService.restoreSessions();\n   525→\n   526→  // F-013: Set up notification callback for session timeout\n   527→  sessionContextService.setNotificationCallback(async (sessionKey, userId) => {\n   528→    try {\n   529→      // Extract chat ID from session key (format: telegram:123456789)\n   530→      const chatId = sessionKey.replace('telegram:', '');\n   531→      await bot.telegram.sendMessage(chatId, '⏰ 会话因长时间未活动已超时，相关状态已清理。');\n   532→    } catch (error) {\n   533→      logger.warn({ sessionKey, userId, error: error.message }, 'Failed to send session timeout notification');\n   534→    }\n   535→  });\n   536→\n   537→  // F-013: Start timeout watcher\n   538→  sessionContextService.startTimeoutWatcher();\n   539→\n   540→  // F-014: Initialize scheduled task service\n   541→  scheduledTaskService.initScheduledTaskService({\n   542→    dataDir: config.systemMonitorDataDir,\n   543→    tasksFile: config.scheduledTasksPath,\n   544→    maxTasks: config.maxScheduledTasks\n   545→  });\n   546→\n   547→  // F-014: Set up task execution callback\n   548→  scheduledTaskService.setExecuteCallback(async ({ command, cwd, sessionId, userId }) => {\n   549→    try {\n   550→      return await executeCommand({\n   551→        command,\n   552→        cwd,\n   553→        sessionId,\n   554→        userId,\n   555→        skipConfirmation: true // Skip confirmation for scheduled tasks\n   556→      });\n   557→    } catch (error) {\n   558→      return {\n   559→        stdout: '',\n   560→        stderr: error.message,\n   561→        exitCode: 1,\n   562→        timedOut: false\n   563→      };\n   564→    }\n   565→  });\n   566→\n   567→  // F-014: Set up task notification callback\n   568→  scheduledTaskService.setNotificationCallback(async (chatId, task) => {\n   569→    try {\n   570→      const result = task.lastResult || {};\n   571→      const lines = [\n   572→        '⏰ *定时任务完成*',\n   573→        '',\n   574→        `任务ID: \\`${task.id.substring(0, 8)}...\\``,\n   575→        `命令: \\`${escapeMarkdownV2(task.command)}\\``,\n   576→        `执行时间: ${new Date(result.executedAt || Date.now()).toLocaleString()}`,\n   577→        '',\n   578→        `exitCode: ${result.exitCode}`,\n   579→        result.stdout ? `stdout:\\n${truncate(result.stdout, 500)}` : 'stdout: (empty)',\n   580→        result.stderr ? `stderr:\\n${escapeMarkdownV2(truncate(result.stderr, 500))}` : 'stderr: (empty)'\n   581→      ];\n   582→      await bot.telegram.sendMessage(chatId, lines.join('\\n'), { parse_mode: 'MarkdownV2' });\n   583→    } catch (error) {\n   584→      logger.warn({ taskId: task.id, error: error.message }, 'Failed to send task notification');\n   585→    }\n   586→  });\n   587→\n   588→  // F-014: Load and start scheduled tasks\n   589→  await scheduledTaskService.loadTasks();\n   590→  scheduledTaskService.startScheduler();\n   591→\n   592→  // F-014: Initialize file watcher service\n   593→  fileWatcherService.initFileWatcherService({\n   594→    dataDir: config.systemMonitorDataDir,\n   595→    watchersFile: config.fileWatchersPath,\n   596→    maxWatchers: config.maxFileWatchers,\n   597→    debounceMs: config.taskDebounceMs,\n   598→    allowedRoots: config.telegramFileAllowedRoots.length > 0\n   599→      ? config.telegramFileAllowedRoots\n   600→      : [process.cwd()]\n   601→  });\n   602→\n   603→  // F-014: Set up file watcher notification callback\n   604→  fileWatcherService.setNotificationCallback(async (chatId, watcher) => {\n   605→    try {\n   606→      const lines = [\n   607→        '📁 *文件变更检测*',\n   608→        '',\n   609→        `路径: \\`${escapeMarkdownV2(watcher.path)}\\``,\n   610→        `事件: ${watcher.eventType}`,\n   611→        `文件: ${watcher.filename || '(未知)'}`,\n   612→        `时间: ${new Date().toLocaleString()}`\n   613→      ];\n   614→      await bot.telegram.sendMessage(chatId, lines.join('\\n'), { parse_mode: 'MarkdownV2' });\n   615→    } catch (error) {\n   616→      logger.warn({ watcherId: watcher.id, error: error.message }, 'Failed to send file watcher notification');\n   617→    }\n   618→  });\n   619→\n   620→  // F-014: Restore file watchers\n   621→  await fileWatcherService.restoreWatches();\n   622→\n   623→  // Register pipeline commands\n   624→  registerPipelineCommands();\n   625→\n   626→  // F-018: Create unified message router for bidirectional sync\n   627→  const messageRouter = createMessageRouter({\n   628→    aiCliExecutor: executeAiCli,\n   629→    sessionStore,\n   630→    realtimeHub\n   631→  });\n   632→\n   633→  // F-018: Initialize session bind service for cross-channel push\n   634→  const sessionBind = createSessionBindService({\n   635→    bindingsPath: config.sessionBindingsPath\n   636→  });\n   637→\n   638→  // F-018: Cross-channel push — forward web-originated AI replies to bound Telegram chats.\n   639→  // Track active subscriptions to avoid duplicates.\n   640→  const crossChannelSubs = new Map(); // sessionKey -> unsubscribe fn\n   641→\n   642→  /**\n   643→   * Subscribe to realtimeHub for a specific Telegram chat session key.\n   644→   * When a web-originated assistant_done event arrives, push the reply to Telegram.\n   645→   */\n   646→  function subscribeCrossChannel(telegramChatId) {\n   647→    const sessionKey = `telegram:${telegramChatId}`;\n   648→    if (crossChannelSubs.has(sessionKey)) {\n   649→      return; // already subscribed\n   650→    }\n   651→\n   652→    const unsubscribe = realtimeHub.subscribe(sessionKey, (event) => {\n   653→      // Only forward assistant_done events from web channel\n   654→      if (event.type === 'assistant_done' && event.payload?.channel === 'web') {\n   655→        const reply = event.payload.reply;\n   656→        if (reply) {\n   657→          const chunks = splitMessage(reply);\n   658→          for (const chunk of chunks) {\n   659→            bot.telegram.sendMessage(telegramChatId, chunk).catch((err) => {\n   660→              logger.warn(\n   661→                { telegramChatId, err: err.message },\n   662→                'F-018: Failed to push web-originated reply to Telegram'\n   663→              );\n   664→            });\n   665→          }\n   666→        }\n   667→      }\n   668→\n   669→      // Forward user_message events from web channel to notify Telegram\n   670→      if (event.type === 'user_message' && event.payload?.channel === 'web') {\n   671→        const msg = event.payload.message;\n   672→        if (msg) {\n   673→          bot.telegram.sendMessage(\n   674→            telegramChatId,\n   675→            `[Web] ${msg.length > 200 ? msg.substring(0, 200) + '...' : msg}`\n   676→          ).catch((err) => {\n   677→            logger.warn(\n   678→              { telegramChatId, err: err.message },\n   679→              'F-018: Failed to push web user message notification to Telegram'\n   680→            );\n   681→          });\n   682→        }\n   683→      }\n   684→    });\n   685→\n   686→    crossChannelSubs.set(sessionKey, unsubscribe);\n   687→    logger.info({ sessionKey }, 'F-018: Cross-channel push subscription active');\n   688→  }\n   689→\n   690→  // Subscribe for all existing bindings on startup\n   691→  // Wait for sessionBind to initialize before reading bindings\n   692→  sessionBind.init().then(() => {\n   693→    const allBindings = sessionBind.getAllBindings();\n   694→    for (const telegramChatId of new Set(Object.values(allBindings))) {\n   695→      subscribeCrossChannel(telegramChatId);\n   696→    }\n   697→    logger.info(\n   698→      { boundChats: Object.keys(allBindings).length },\n   699→      'F-018: Cross-channel push initialized for existing bindings'\n   700→    );\n   701→  }).catch((err) => {\n   702→    logger.error({ err: err.message }, 'F-018: Failed to initialize cross-channel push');\n   703→  });\n   704→\n   705→  // Expose subscribeCrossChannel for dynamic binding (called when new bindings are created)\n   706→  bot._f018 = { subscribeCrossChannel, sessionBind, messageRouter };\n   707→\n   708→  bot.catch(async (error, ctx) => {\n   709→    const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n   710→    logger.error({ err: message, chatId: ctx?.chat?.id, updateType: ctx?.updateType }, 'Unhandled error while processing telegram update');\n   711→    try {\n   712→      if (ctx?.chat?.id) {\n   713→        await ctx.telegram.sendMessage(ctx.chat.id, '处理请求时出现异常，请重试一次。');\n   714→      }\n   715→    } catch (notifyError) {\n   716→      logger.warn({ err: notifyError instanceof Error ? notifyError.message : String(notifyError) }, 'Failed to notify user after unhandled telegram error');\n   717→    }\n   718→  });\n   719→\n   720→  bot.start(async (ctx) => {\n   721→    await ctx.reply('PrizmClaw 已启动。可直接聊天，也可用 /help 查看可用命令。');\n   722→  });\n   723→\n   724→  bot.help(async (ctx) => {\n   725→    const helpText = generateHelp();\n   726→    await ctx.reply(helpText);\n   727→  });\n   728→\n   729→  bot.command('reset', async (ctx) => {\n   730→    try {\n   731→      ensureAllowed(ctx);\n   732→      const sessionId = buildSessionId(ctx);\n   733→\n   734→      // F-011: Interrupt any running AI CLI task\n   735→      if (isAiCliRunning(sessionId)) {\n   736→        interruptAiCli(sessionId);\n   737→      }\n   738→\n   739→      resetSession({ channel: 'telegram', sessionId });\n   740→      await ctx.reply('已清空当前会话上下文。');\n   741→    } catch (error) {\n   742→      await ctx.reply(error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error));\n   743→    }\n   744→  });\n   745→\n   746→  bot.command('screenshot', async (ctx) => {\n   747→    try {\n   748→      ensureAllowed(ctx);\n   749→      await ctx.reply('正在获取截图。');\n   750→      const { buffer } = await captureScreenshot();\n   751→      await ctx.replyWithPhoto({ source: buffer }, { caption: '当前本地屏幕截图' });\n   752→    } catch (error) {\n   753→      const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n   754→      logger.error({ err: message }, 'Failed to capture screenshot in telegram');\n   755→      await ctx.reply(`截图失败：${message}`);\n   756→    }\n   757→  });\n   758→\n   759→  bot.command('exec', async (ctx) => {\n   760→    try {\n   761→      ensureAllowed(ctx);\n   762→      const payload = ctx.message.text.replace('/exec', '').trim();\n   763→      if (!payload) {\n   764→        await ctx.reply('请提供命令，例如 /exec pwd');\n   765→        return;\n   766→      }\n   767→\n   768→      const sessionId = buildSessionId(ctx);\n   769→      const userId = ctx.from?.id;\n   770→\n   771→      await ctx.reply('正在执行命令...');\n   772→      const result = await executeCommand({\n   773→        command: payload,\n   774→        sessionId,\n   775→        userId\n   776→      });\n   777→\n   778→      // Handle confirmation required\n   779→      if (result.needsConfirmation) {\n   780→        await ctx.reply(result.confirmationMessage);\n   781→        return;\n   782→      }\n   783→\n   784→      // Send output\n   785→      await replyLargeText(ctx, result.output);\n   786→\n   787→      // Indicate if more pages available\n   788→      if (result.hasMorePages) {\n   789→        await ctx.reply('📄 输出已截断。使用 /more 查看更多内容。');\n   790→      }\n   791→    } catch (error) {\n   792→      const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n   793→      logger.error({ err: message }, 'Failed to exec command in telegram');\n   794→      await ctx.reply(`执行失败：${message}`);\n   795→    }\n   796→  });\n   797→\n   798→  // F-009: /cd command handler\n   799→  bot.command('cd', async (ctx) => {\n   800→    try {\n   801→      ensureAllowed(ctx);\n   802→      const payload = ctx.message.text.replace('/cd', '').trim();\n   803→      const sessionId = buildSessionId(ctx);\n   804→\n   805→      await handleCd({\n   806→        ctx,\n   807→        reply: (msg) => ctx.reply(msg),\n   808→        params: {},\n   809→        userId: ctx.from?.id,\n   810→        sessionId,\n   811→        args: payload ? [payload] : []\n   812→      });\n   813→    } catch (error) {\n   814→      const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n   815→      logger.error({ err: message }, 'Failed to cd in telegram');\n   816→      await ctx.reply(`切换目录失败：${message}`);\n   817→    }\n   818→  });\n   819→\n   820→  // F-009: /more command handler\n   821→  bot.command('more', async (ctx) => {\n   822→    try {\n   823→      ensureAllowed(ctx);\n   824→      const sessionId = buildSessionId(ctx);\n   825→\n   826→      await handleMore({\n   827→        ctx,\n   828→        reply: (msg) => ctx.reply(msg),\n   829→        params: {},\n   830→        userId: ctx.from?.id,\n   831→        sessionId\n   832→      });\n   833→    } catch (error) {\n   834→      const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n   835→      logger.error({ err: message }, 'Failed to get more output in telegram');\n   836→      await ctx.reply(`获取更多输出失败：${message}`);\n   837→    }\n   838→  });\n   839→\n   840→  // T-100: Document upload handler for plan files\n   841→  bot.on('document', async (ctx) => {\n   842→    try {\n   843→      ensureAllowed(ctx);\n   844→\n   845→      const document = ctx.message?.document;\n   846→      if (!document) {\n   847→        return;\n   848→      }\n   849→\n   850→      // Check file extension\n   851→      const fileName = document.file_name || '';\n   852→      const ext = path.extname(fileName).toLowerCase();\n   853→\n   854→      if (ext !== '.json') {\n   855→        // Not a JSON file, ignore silently (other handlers may process it)\n   856→        return;\n   857→      }\n   858→\n   859→      // Check file size\n   860→      const fileSize = document.file_size || 0;\n   861→      if (fileSize > 1024 * 1024) { // 1MB limit\n   862→        await ctx.reply('❌ 文件过大，限制 1MB。');\n   863→        return;\n   864→      }\n   865→\n   866→      await ctx.reply('正在处理上传的计划文件...');\n   867→\n   868→      // Download file content\n   869→      const fileLink = await ctx.telegram.getFileLink(document.file_id);\n   870→      const fileUrl = fileLink.href || fileLink.toString();\n   871→\n   872→      const response = await fetch(fileUrl);\n   873→      if (!response.ok) {\n   874→        throw new Error(`下载文件失败: ${response.status}`);\n   875→      }\n   876→\n   877→      const content = await response.text();\n   878→\n   879→      // Validate and save using plan-ingestion-service\n   880→      const infraConfig = loadPipelineInfraConfig();\n   881→      const planService = createPlanIngestionService({ plansDir: infraConfig.plansDir });\n   882→\n   883→      const validationResult = planService.validate(content);\n   884→\n   885→      if (!validationResult.valid) {\n   886→        const errorMsg = planService.formatValidationErrors(validationResult.errors);\n   887→        await ctx.reply(errorMsg);\n   888→        return;\n   889→      }\n   890→\n   891→      // Save the plan\n   892→      const saveResult = await planService.save(\n   893→        validationResult.type,\n   894→        content,\n   895→        { uploadedBy: ctx.from?.id }\n   896→      );\n   897→\n   898→      if (!saveResult.success) {\n   899→        await ctx.reply('❌ 保存失败，请稍后重试。');\n   900→        return;\n   901→      }\n   902→\n   903→      // Set as current version\n   904→      await planService.setCurrent(validationResult.type, saveResult.version);\n   905→\n   906→      // Format success message\n   907→      const typeDisplay = validationResult.type === 'feature-list' ? '特性列表' : 'Bug修复列表';\n   908→      const summary = validationResult.summary;\n   909→\n   910→      await ctx.reply([\n   911→        `✅ ${typeDisplay}已保存并激活`,\n   912→        `版本: ${saveResult.version}`,\n   913→        `名称: ${summary?.name || '未知'}`,\n   914→        `项目数: ${summary?.itemCount || 0}`,\n   915→        '',\n   916→        summary?.statusBreakdown ? '状态分布:' : '',\n   917→        ...Object.entries(summary?.statusBreakdown || {}).map(([status, count]) => `  ${status}: ${count}`)\n   918→      ].filter(Boolean).join('\\n'));\n   919→\n   920→    } catch (error) {\n   921→      const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n   922→      logger.error({ err: message }, 'Failed to process document upload');\n   923→      await ctx.reply(`❌ 处理失败：${message}`);\n   924→    }\n   925→  });\n   926→\n   927→  bot.on('text', async (ctx) => {\n   928→    // Check for pipeline commands first\n   929→    const handled = await routeCommand(ctx);\n   930→    if (handled) {\n   931→      return;\n   932→    }\n   933→\n   934→    const sessionId = buildSessionId(ctx);\n   935→    const userId = ctx.from?.id;\n   936→\n   937→    // F-009: Direct exec mode - treat plain text as command when enabled\n   938→    if (config.directExecMode && config.enableSystemExec) {\n   939→      try {\n   940→        ensureAllowed(ctx);\n   941→        const command = ctx.message.text;\n   942→\n   943→        // Skip if it looks like a chat message (contains Chinese or Japanese characters, etc.)\n   944→        const isLikelyChat = /[\\u4e00-\\u9fff\\u3040-\\u309f\\u30a0-\\u30ff]/.test(command);\n   945→\n   946→        if (!isLikelyChat) {\n   947→          await ctx.reply('正在执行命令...');\n   948→          const result = await executeCommand({\n   949→            command,\n   950→            sessionId,\n   951→            userId\n   952→          });\n   953→\n   954→          if (result.needsConfirmation) {\n   955→            await ctx.reply(result.confirmationMessage);\n   956→            return;\n   957→          }\n   958→\n   959→          await replyLargeText(ctx, result.output);\n   960→\n   961→          if (result.hasMorePages) {\n   962→            await ctx.reply('📄 输出已截断。使用 /more 查看更多内容。');\n   963→          }\n   964→          return;\n   965→        }\n   966→      } catch (error) {\n   967→        const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n   968→        // If exec fails, fall through to chat mode\n   969→        logger.warn({ err: message }, 'Direct exec mode failed, falling back to chat');\n   970→      }\n   971→    }\n   972→\n   973→    // F-011: Check if AI CLI is already running\n   974→    if (isAiCliRunning(sessionId)) {\n   975→      await ctx.reply('⏳ 有任务正在执行，请等待完成或使用 /stop 中断。');\n   976→      return;\n   977→    }\n   978→\n   979→    let typingTimer = null;\n   980→\n   981→    try {\n   982→      ensureAllowed(ctx);\n   983→      await ctx.sendChatAction('typing');\n   984→\n   985→      const streamPublisher = createEditableStreamPublisher(ctx);\n   986→      typingTimer = setInterval(() => {\n   987→        ctx.sendChatAction('typing').catch(() => undefined);\n   988→      }, TYPING_INTERVAL_MS);\n   989→\n   990→      // F-018: Use message-router for unified processing\n   991→      const sessionKey = `telegram:${sessionId}`;\n   992→\n   993→      // Track last heartbeat message for updates\n   994→      /** @type {{ message_id: number } | null} */\n   995→      let lastHeartbeatMsg = null;\n   996→\n   997→      const routerResult = await messageRouter.processMessage({\n   998→        channel: 'telegram',\n   999→        sessionId,\n  1000→        message: ctx.message.text,\n  1001→        telegramChatId: sessionId,\n  1002→        userId,\n  1003→        hooks: {\n  1004→          onStatus: (payload) => {\n  1005→            if (payload.stage === 'running') {\n  1006→              ctx.sendChatAction('typing').catch(() => undefined);\n  1007→            }\n  1008→          },\n  1009→          onAssistantChunk: (data) => {\n  1010→            streamPublisher.push(data.text);\n  1011→          },\n  1012→          onAssistantDone: (data) => {\n  1013→            // Done event handled below after processMessage resolves\n  1014→          }\n  1015→        }\n  1016→      });\n  1017→\n  1018→      // Delete heartbeat message if exists\n  1019→      if (lastHeartbeatMsg) {\n  1020→        ctx.telegram.deleteMessage(ctx.chat.id, lastHeartbeatMsg.message_id).catch(() => {});\n  1021→      }\n  1022→\n  1023→      const replyText = routerResult.reply;\n  1024→\n  1025→      // Extract file markers and send\n  1026→      const { fileRefs, cleanedText } = extractFileMarkers(replyText);\n  1027→      logger.info({ sessionId, fileRefsCount: fileRefs.length, fileRefs }, 'Parsed file markers from assistant reply');\n  1028→      const finalText = cleanedText || (fileRefs.length > 0 ? '已执行，正在发送文件。' : '已执行。');\n  1029→\n  1030→      streamPublisher.setFinalText(finalText);\n  1031→      const streamed = await streamPublisher.finish();\n  1032→      if (streamed.outputLength === 0) {\n  1033→        await replyLargeText(ctx, finalText);\n  1034→      }\n  1035→\n  1036→      if (fileRefs.length > 0) {\n  1037→        const fileSendResults = await replyFiles(ctx, fileRefs);\n  1038→        const failed = fileSendResults.filter((item) => !item.sent);\n  1039→\n  1040→        if (failed.length === 0) {\n  1041→          await safeReply(ctx, `已发送 ${fileSendResults.length} 个文件。`);\n  1042→        } else {\n  1043→          const failedList = failed\n  1044→            .map((item) => {\n  1045→              const reason =\n  1046→                item.reason === 'relative_path_not_allowed'\n  1047→                  ? '仅允许绝对路径，拒绝相对路径（请使用 SEND_FILE:/var/folders/.../xxx.png）'\n  1048→                  : item.reason === 'not_found'\n  1049→                    ? '文件不存在或不可访问（建议返回绝对路径，例如 SEND_FILE:/var/folders/.../xxx.png）'\n  1050→                    : item.reason;\n  1051→              const tried = Array.isArray(item.triedPaths) && item.triedPaths.length > 0 ? `；尝试路径：${item.triedPaths.join(' | ')}` : '';\n  1052→              return `- SEND_FILE:${item.fileRef}${reason ? `（${reason}）` : ''}${tried}`;\n  1053→            })\n  1054→            .join('\\n');\n  1055→          await safeReply(ctx, `以下文件发送失败，已附回原始引用：\\n${failedList}`);\n  1056→          logger.warn({ sessionId, failed }, 'Some files failed to send to telegram');\n  1057→        }\n  1058→      }\n  1059→    } catch (error) {\n  1060→      const message = error instanceof Error ? error.message : String(error);\n  1061→      logger.error({ err: message, sessionId }, 'Failed to process telegram message');\n  1062→      await safeReply(ctx, `处理失败：${message}`);\n  1063→    } finally {\n  1064→      if (typingTimer) {\n  1065→        clearInterval(typingTimer);\n  1066→      }\n  1067→    }\n  1068→  });\n  1069→\n  1070→  return bot;\n  1071→}\n  1072→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01YQWojDuu9hhr9G6EMSopGA","session_id":"1825d45b-0e87-4048-aee3-8c65afe6c801","uuid":"ea113261-2c46-407e-b3bb-9ffc5f0d7c2d","timestamp":"2026-03-22T06:45:25.336Z"}
