{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_vrtx_01YQWojDuu9hhr9G6EMSopGA","type":"tool_result","content":[{"text":"---\n\n## COMPLETION_SIGNAL\n\n**Feature**: F-018 Web-Telegram Bidirectional Sync\n**Phase**: 6 (Review)\n**Verdict**: **PASS_WITH_WARNINGS**\n\n### Summary\n\nAll 41 F-018 tests pass across 3 test suites (unit + integration). The implementation correctly achieves the target architecture: both Web and Telegram channels route through `messageRouter.processMessage()`, sharing session state via unified session keys and publishing events through `realtimeHub` for cross-channel sync. All 6 acceptance criteria are architecturally implemented.\n\n### HIGH Finding Requiring Follow-up\n\n**F4** (HIGH, spec-compliance): When a new session binding is created at runtime via `POST /api/bind`, the Telegram bot does not subscribe to `realtimeHub` for that newly bound session. Cross-channel push (Web-to-Telegram forwarding) only works for bindings that exist when the bot starts. The `bot._f018.subscribeCrossChannel` function was exposed for this purpose but is never called from the bind endpoint. This should be wired in a follow-up iteration.\n\n### Files Reviewed\n\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/services/session-bind.js` (modified)\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/bot/telegram.js` (modified)\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/http/server.js` (modified)\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/routes/api-routes.js` (modified)\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/services/message-router.js` (verified, no changes needed)\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/services/index.js` (verified, no changes needed)\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/tests/services/session-bind-f018.test.js` (modified)\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/tests/services/message-router.test.js` (reviewed)\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/tests/integration/f018-web-telegram-sync.integration.test.js` (modified)\n\nReview notes appended to `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/018-web-telegram-bidirectional-sync/context-snapshot.md`.","type":"text"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a05e6abfc57f009af (use SendMessage with to: 'a05e6abfc57f009af' to continue this agent)\n<usage>total_tokens: 88404\ntool_uses: 21\nduration_ms: 160748</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1825d45b-0e87-4048-aee3-8c65afe6c801","uuid":"1c163568-7c50-49e6-901e-f238e4da2d44","timestamp":"2026-03-22T06:47:46.644Z","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read /Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.claude/agents/prizm-dev-team-reviewer.md. For feature F-018 (slug: 018-web-telegram-bidirectional-sync):\n\n**IMPORTANT**: Read `.prizmkit/specs/018-web-telegram-bidirectional-sync/context-snapshot.md` FIRST.\n\n1. Read `.prizmkit/specs/018-web-telegram-bidirectional-sync/context-snapshot.md`:\n   - Section 3: Prizm Context (RULES, PATTERNS to check against)\n   - Section 4: File Manifest (original file structure)\n   - '## Implementation Log': what Dev changed, key decisions, discoveries\n2. Run prizmkit-code-review: spec compliance (against the acceptance criteria in Section 1), code quality, correctness. Read ONLY files listed in Implementation Log.\n3. Write and execute integration tests covering all user stories from the acceptance criteria. Use `TEST_CMD=node --test tests/services/session-bind-f018.test.js tests/services/message-router.test.js tests/integration/f018-web-telegram-sync.integration.test.js` — do NOT try alternative test commands.\n4. Append '## Review Notes' to context-snapshot.md: issues found (with severity), test results, final verdict.\n\nReport verdict: PASS, PASS_WITH_WARNINGS, or NEEDS_FIXES.","agentId":"a05e6abfc57f009af","content":[{"text":"---\n\n## COMPLETION_SIGNAL\n\n**Feature**: F-018 Web-Telegram Bidirectional Sync\n**Phase**: 6 (Review)\n**Verdict**: **PASS_WITH_WARNINGS**\n\n### Summary\n\nAll 41 F-018 tests pass across 3 test suites (unit + integration). The implementation correctly achieves the target architecture: both Web and Telegram channels route through `messageRouter.processMessage()`, sharing session state via unified session keys and publishing events through `realtimeHub` for cross-channel sync. All 6 acceptance criteria are architecturally implemented.\n\n### HIGH Finding Requiring Follow-up\n\n**F4** (HIGH, spec-compliance): When a new session binding is created at runtime via `POST /api/bind`, the Telegram bot does not subscribe to `realtimeHub` for that newly bound session. Cross-channel push (Web-to-Telegram forwarding) only works for bindings that exist when the bot starts. The `bot._f018.subscribeCrossChannel` function was exposed for this purpose but is never called from the bind endpoint. This should be wired in a follow-up iteration.\n\n### Files Reviewed\n\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/services/session-bind.js` (modified)\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/bot/telegram.js` (modified)\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/http/server.js` (modified)\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/routes/api-routes.js` (modified)\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/services/message-router.js` (verified, no changes needed)\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/src/services/index.js` (verified, no changes needed)\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/tests/services/session-bind-f018.test.js` (modified)\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/tests/services/message-router.test.js` (reviewed)\n- `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/tests/integration/f018-web-telegram-sync.integration.test.js` (modified)\n\nReview notes appended to `/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizmkit/specs/018-web-telegram-bidirectional-sync/context-snapshot.md`.","type":"text"}],"totalDurationMs":160748,"totalTokens":88404,"totalToolUseCount":21,"usage":{"input_tokens":1404,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":86370,"ou