{"type":"assistant","message":{"content":[{"id":"toolu_vrtx_01AcdxfN5BioegoFKraAuttt","input":{"file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizm-docs/services.prizm","content":"MODULE: src/services\nFILES: 30\nRESPONSIBILITY: Core service layer — AI CLI execution, session management, messaging, pipeline control, monitoring\nINTERFACES:\n- executeAiCli(options): Promise<AiCliExecutionResult> — unified AI CLI executor with process tracking\n- interruptAiCli(sessionId): {ok, pid?, error?} — interrupt running AI task\n- createMessageRouter({aiCliExecutor, sessionStore, realtimeHub}): MessageRouter — F-018 unified message processor\n- processMessage({channel, sessionId, message, telegramChatId?, userId?, hooks?}): Promise<{reply}> — route message through AI CLI\n- createSessionBindService({bindingsPath}): SessionBindingService — F-018 factory with deferred init\n- SessionBindingService.bindSession(webId, chatId): {ok} — bind web session to Telegram chat\n- SessionBindingService.getBoundChatId(webId): string|null — lookup binding\n- SessionBindingService.getBoundWebSessions(chatId): string[] — reverse lookup\n- SessionBindingService.ensureReady(): Promise<void> — wait for deferred init\n- sessionStore.append(key, role, content) — append message to session\n- sessionStore.toPrompt(key, channel): string — build prompt with context\n- realtimeHub.subscribe(key, listener): unsubscribe — SSE event pub/sub\n- realtimeHub.publish(key, event) — broadcast event to subscribers\n- chatWithSession({channel, sessionId, message, realtimeHooks}): Promise<reply> — legacy Web chat (deprecated by F-018)\nDEPENDENCIES:\n- uses: node:child_process: spawn for AI CLI process\n- uses: zod: config validation\n- uses: node:fs/promises: session persistence, bindings file\n- imports: src/config.js: runtime configuration\n- imports: src/security/guard.js: sanitizeInput\nKEY_FILES:\n- ai-cli-service.js: AI CLI executor with heartbeat, timeout, metrics (564 lines)\n- message-router.js: F-018 unified message processor (128 lines)\n- session-bind.js: F-018 session binding with persistence (~220 lines)\n- session-store.js: in-memory session state (427 lines)\n- realtime-hub.js: SSE event pub/sub (35 lines)\n- chat-service.js: legacy chat via codebuddy adapter (80 lines, deprecated)\nTRAPS:\n- SessionBindingService uses deferred init — always call ensureReady() before sync methods in async contexts\n- SessionBindingService persistence is fire-and-forget — tests must call flush() to verify file writes\n- messageRouter does not expose heartbeat hooks — Telegram heartbeat progress disabled after F-018 migration\n- Runtime bindings created via POST /api/bind do NOT auto-subscribe realtimeHub for cross-channel push (F-018 gap)\nUPDATED: 2026-03-22\n"},"name":"Write","type":"tool_use"}],"id":"req_vrtx_011CZHfy94H2Ax1ut7tsPNnA","model":"claude-opus-4-6","role":"assistant","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":499,"output_tokens":25,"cache_read_input_tokens":123453},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1825d45b-0e87-4048-aee3-8c65afe6c801","uuid":"adc0cc7b-1244-4d00-b8b0-818b8dfe103f"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"content":[{"id":"toolu_vrtx_01V5fgKyFhjh4bzSx4h8TuV9","input":{"file_path":"/Users/loneyu/SelfProjects/PrizmClaw/.prizm-docs/bot.prizm","content":"MODULE: src/bot\nFILES: 8 (+30 command handlers in commands/handlers/)\nRESPONSIBILITY: Telegram bot — message handling, command routing, file delivery, streaming output\nINTERFACES:\n- createTelegramBot(): Promise<Telegraf> — initialize bot with all command handlers and services\n- bot._f018.subscribeCrossChannel(chatId): void — subscribe realtimeHub for cross-channel push\nKEY_FILES:\n- telegram.js: Main bot setup, text handler, file handling, stream publisher (~1013 lines)\n- commands/index.js: Command registry and routing\n- commands/help.js: Help text generation\nDEPENDENCIES:\n- uses: telegraf: Telegram bot framework\n- imports: src/services/ai-cli-service.js: executeAiCli, interruptAiCli\n- imports: src/services/message-router.js: F-018 unified message routing\n- imports: src/services/session-bind.js: F-018 session binding for cross-channel\n- imports: src/services/realtime-hub.js: F-018 event subscription for cross-channel push\n- imports: src/services/session-store.js: session state\n- imports: src/services/chat-service.js: legacy (still imported for /reset command)\nTRAPS:\n- Telegram bot text handler uses messageRouter.processMessage() (F-018) — no longer calls executeAiCli directly\n- Cross-channel push only subscribes for bindings that exist at bot startup; dynamic bindings via API need manual subscribeCrossChannel() call\n- Heartbeat progress messages disabled after F-018 migration to messageRouter (messageRouter lacks onHeartbeat hook)\n- bot._f018 is an internal namespace — not a stable public API\nUPDATED: 2026-03-22\n"},"name":"Write","type":"tool_use"}],"id":"req_vrtx_011CZHfy94H2Ax1ut7tsPNnA","model":"claude-opus-4-6","role":"assistant","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"type":"message","usage":{"input_tokens":499,"output_tokens":25,"cache_read_input_tokens":123453